# Telemetry dashboard environment variables.
#
# This app is a static export (see spec/22). Anything prefixed
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ is baked into the build and shipped to the browser;
# per spec/06 the repo is public, so never put secrets here.

# Where the dashboard fetches GET /api/telemetry/summary from. In
# production the router stitches the api worker onto the same hostname
# under `/api/*`, so leaving this unset is correct (the page falls back
# to the origin-relative '/api', which the router rewrites).
#
# For local development you'll want to override this, otherwise the
# fetch hits the Next dev server (3003) and 404s. Two common targets:
#
# - Point at a local `wrangler dev` of @livediagram/api (recommended):
#     NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://localhost:8787/api
#
# - Point at the deployed API (reads production telemetry):
#     NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=https://www.livediagram.app/api
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and edit. `.env.local` is gitignored.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=
